        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1828-29" script="cursive" medium="pencil"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>description of <geogName corresp="#SKIDDAW">skiddaw</geogName> &#x0026;<lb/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/><geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">lake derwent</geogName></head>
                <ab>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l><geogName corresp="#SKIDDAW">Skiddaw</geogName> upon thy heights the<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>sun shines bright</l>
                        <l>but only for a moment then<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>gives place</l> 
                        <l>Unto a playful cloud which on<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>thy brow</l>
                        <l>Sports wantonly then floats<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>away in air</l>
                        <l>throwing its shadow on thy<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>towering height</l>
                        <l>And darkens for a moment<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>thy green side</l>
                        <l>But adds unto its beauty as it<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>makes</l>
                        <l>the sun more bright when it<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>again appears</l>
                <pb facs="1229226v"/>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">Now hear my boyish moral</del></l>
                        <l>Then in the morning on thy<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>brow those clouds</l>
                        <l>Rest, as upon a couch and give<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>fair <del rend="strikethrough"><unclear reason="illegible" resp="#DCH">voi</unclear></del><!--CWB: There shouldn't be a space before an above- or below-the-line addition like the one that follows.--><add place="below"><!--CWB: <space> added.--><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>scope</add><!-- DCH: I changed quantity 13 to 6 since I think the program isn't counting characters in the main line but in the runover --></l> 
                        <l>For fancys play. And airy for<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>tresses<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#FORTRESSESGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>and towers battlements and<lb type="runover"/><!--CWB: @quantity in the following <space> increased by 1 to include the space at the beginning of this line.--><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>all appear.<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#PAUSEPERIOD"/></l>
                        <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>chasing the other off and in<lb type="runover"/><!--CWB: @quantity in the following <space> increased by 1 to include the space at the beginning of this line.--><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>their turn</l>
                        <l><space quantity="2" unit="chars"/>are chased by the others.<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#CHASEGLOSS"/> But<lb type="runover"/><!--CWB: @quantity in the following <space> decreased by 1 to account for the apparent negative space (-1 space) at the beginning of the following runover.--><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>enough</l>
                        <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>Ive treated of the clouds.<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#PAUSEPERIOD2"/> now<lb type="runover"/><!--CWB: @quantity in the following <space> increased by 1 to include the space at the beginning of this line.--><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/><geogName corresp="#SKIDDAW">skiddaw</geogName> come<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#SKIDDAWCOMEGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l>noble and grand and beutious<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>clothed with green</l>
                        <l>and yet but scantily and in<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>some parts</l>
                        <l>a bare terrific cliff precipitous</l>
                        <l>descends with only here &#x0026;<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>there a root</l>
                        <!--CWB: Original encoding was <l><del rend="overwritten">straggling as <unclear reason="illeglible" resp="#DCH">it push its tendons</unclear></del><add rend="overwriting"><handShift new="#HANDJR1828-29" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>a straggler there as tho grow with stone</add><lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/><del rend="overwritten"><handShift new="#HANDJR1828-29" script="cursive" medium="pencil"/>from the cliff</del><add rend="overwriting"><handShift new="#HANDJR1828-29" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>for earth</add></l>. I've re-encoded this <l> below:-->
                        <l><subst><add><handShift medium="ink"/>a straggler. there as tho grow with stone<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10"/>for earth</add><del rend="overwriting">straggling as <unclear reason="illeglible" resp="#DCH">it push its branches</unclear><lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>from the cliff</del></subst><ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#STRAGGLERGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l><!--CWB: A <handShift> is actually NOT needed here because the previous one - to ink - hasn't ended; but shouldn't the following be encoded as an addition - as I have encoded it here?--><add rend="overwriting">and bare and scraggy as befit the <lb type="runover"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>cliff</add><ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#ARRETEZGLOSS"/></l>
                    </lg>
                </ab>
                <pb facs="1229226r"/>
                    <!--  <floatingText>
                        <body>
                            <div>
                                CWB: I changed the <p>s below to "anonymous blocks," <ab>s, since they don't actually appear to be paragraphs.
                                <ab><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>Play</ab>
                                <ab>CWB: If we were to borrow from the Kempe Project, there IS actually a way to encode the "box" around the text that follows.<del rend="strikethrough">arretez Oh arretez</del><ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#ARRETEZGLOSS"/></ab>
                            </div>
                        </body>
                    </floatingText>
                    CWB: Simplified alternative to the <floatingText> encoded above - without the "box":
                    <lb/><ab><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>Play</ab>
                    <lb/><ab><del rend="strikethrough">arretez Oh arretez</del></ab>
                    --> 
                <ab>
                    <lg type="stanza">    
                        <l><geogName corresp="#SKIDDAW">Sciddaw</geogName> majestic <del rend="strikethrough"><geogName corresp="#SKIDDAW">skiddaw</geogName></del><add place="above"><space quantity="18" unit="chars"/>giant natures</add><lb type="runover"/><space quantity="18" unit="chars"/>work</l>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">lower</del><add place="above"><space quantity="3" unit="chars"/>For less</add> than <geogName corresp="#ALPS">alps</geogName> or <geogName corresp="#ANDES">andes</geogName> <del rend="strikethrough"><geogName corresp="#PYRENEES">pyrenees</geogName></del></l>
                        <l><del rend="scratchout"><unclear reason="illegible" resp="#DCH">are</unclear></del> all much higher<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_contextual.php#HIGHERGLOSS"/> but those</l>
                        <l>those giant works of art<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_contextual.php#PYRAMIDSGLOSS"/> with<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>thee compared</l>
                        <l>sink into nothing, all that<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>art can do</l>
                        <l>is nothing beside thee The<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="11" unit="chars"/>touch of man</l>
                        <l>raised pigmy mountains but<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>gigantic tombs</l>
                        <l>the touch of nature raised<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>the mountains<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>brow</l>
                        <l>But made no tombs at all save where<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="14" unit="chars"/>the snow</l>
                        <l>the fleecy locks of winter falls around</l>
                        <l>and forms a <del rend="strikethrough">to</del> white tomb for<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="11" unit="chars"/><del rend="strikethrough">a</del><add place="above"><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>the</add> careless swain<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#WHITETOMBGLOSS"/></l>
                <pb facs="1229227v"/>
                        <l><!--CWB: <space> added.--><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>Who wanders far from home and<lb type="runover"/><!--CWB: @quantity in the following <space> increased by 1 to include the space at the beginning of this line.--><space quantity="14" unit="chars"/>meets his death</l>
                        <l>amidst the cold of winter but<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>no more <del rend="strikethrough">on</del></l>
                        <l>on this sad subject on this<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>happy day<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#HAPPYDAYGLOSS"/> <ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#HOLLOPAPAGLOSS"/></l>
                    </lg>
                    <!--CWB: <lb> added.--><lb/>
                <milestone unit="undeclared" rend="hr-full"/>
                </ab>
                <!--CWB: Original encoding was
                    
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <div>
                            <p><del rend="strikethrough">Hollo papa hollo papa
                                <lb/>attend to me what are
                                <lb/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>you</del></p>
                            <p><ref type="witness" target="christs_intercession_msii.php"><title type="sermon" corresp="#SERMONNOTESCHRISTS">Sermon Notes [&#x201C;christs intercession&#x201D;]</title></ref></p>
                        </div>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                
                I've simplified this to:
                    <lb/><ab><del rend="strikethrough">Hollo papa hollo papa<lb/>attend to me what are<lb/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>you</del></ab>
                as that which includes and follows "christ's intercession" appears to belong to a disparate work. This begs the question: does the text immediately above and at the top of 1229226r actually belong to similarly disparate "works?"-->
                
                <pb facs="1229227r"/>
                <ab>
                    <metamark function="resume"><space quantity="4" unit="chars"/>skiddaw derwent water<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#METAMARKGLOSS"/></metamark>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>Now derwent water come a looking<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/>glass</l>
                        <l>wherein reflected are the mountains<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="17" unit="chars"/>heights</l>
                        <l>A stragller pushes forth its<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>branches stiff</l>
                        <l>all<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#ALLGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l>as in a mirror framed in rocks<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>and woods<!--CWB: There is a horizonatl-ish mark on the page here. Is it improtant?--></l>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">upon whose polished surface</del></l>
                        <l>so upon thee there is<lb type="runover"/>a seeming mount</l>
                        <l><space quantity="-1" unit="chars"/>a seeming tree a<lb type="runover"/>seeming rivulet<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#RUNOVERGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">which falls and yet does<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>not fall <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#DCH">pon</unclear> on</del><lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>thee</l>
                        <l>all upon thee are painted<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>by a hand</l>
                        <l>which not a critic can well criticise</l>
                        <l>but to disturb thee oft bluff <persName type="fictional" corresp="#AEOLUS">eolus</persName></l>
                        <l>Descends upon the mountains with his<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/>breath</l>
                        <l>thy polished surface is a boy at play</l>
                        <l><space quantity="4" unit="chars"/>who labours at the snow to<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="3" unit="chars"/>make a man</l>
                <pb facs="1229228v"/>
                        <l>And when he&#x02BC;s made it knocks it<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="15" unit="chars"/>down again<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#MADEITGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l>So when thou&#x02BC;st made a picture<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>thou dost play</l>
                        <l>At tearing it to pieces trees do<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>first</l>
                        <l>Tremble as if a monstrous heart of<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="14" unit="chars"/>oak</l>
                        <l>Were but an aspen leaf and then<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>as if</l>
                        <l>it were a cobweb in the tempests<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>blow</l>
                        <l>Thus like <persName type="fictional" corresp="#PENELOPE">penelope</persName> thou weavst a<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/><del rend="strikethrough">loom</del> web</l>
                        <l>and then thou dost undo it thourt<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/>like her<!--CWB: There are horizontal-ish marks on the page here. Are they important?--></l> 
                        <l>because thourt fair and oft<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/>deceiving too<!--CWB: There are horizontal-ish marks on the page here. Are they important?--><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_contextual.php#PENELOPEGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">first seeming</del> to be calm then<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>turning rough</l>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">and now <persName type="fictional" corresp="#PENELOPE">penelope</persName> <unclear reason="illegible">an</unclear> all good bye</del></l>
                        <l><del rend="strikethrough">my muse I need no farther use of thee</del></l>
                        <l>and thus deceiving as <persName type="fictional" corresp="#PENELOPE">penelope</persName><ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#ROUGHGLOSS"/></l>
                    </lg>
                    <milestone unit="undeclared" rend="hr-full"/>
                </ab>
                <metamark function="resume"><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/>conclusion</metamark>
                <ab>
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>sweet <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">derwent</geogName> on thy winding<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>shore</l>
                        <l>beside<del rend="scratchout">s</del> they mountain forests<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/>hoar</l>
                <pb facs="1229228r"/>
                        <l>there would I like to wander<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="10" unit="chars"/><!--CWB: There appears to be a stray "h" on this "line."-->still</l>
                        <l>and drink from out the rippling<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="12" unit="chars"/>rill</l>
                        <l>Which from thy <del rend="strikethrough">highest</del> <add place="above"><space quantity="19" unit="chars"/>head</add>mountain<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>doth fall<del rend="strikethrough">s</del><ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#DOTHFALLGLOSS"/></l>
                        <l>And mingles with the<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>eagles call</l>
                        <l>While on <geogName corresp="#HELVELLYN">helvellyn</geogName> thunder<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="6" unit="chars"/>roars</l>
                        <l>reechoed from old<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#FROMOLDGLOSS"/> <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">derwent</geogName>s<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="13" unit="chars"/>shores</l>
                        <l>and where the lightning<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/>flashes still</l>
                        <l>reflected in the mountain<lb type="runover"/><space quantity="8" unit="chars"/>rill</l>
                    </lg>
                    <milestone unit="undeclared" rend="hr-full"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
        </body>
